# IMS Manager (assisted by IMS Consultant)

The IMS Manager, assisted by IMS Consultants, manages the Made Tech internal audit and management meeting programme and ensures the IMS documentation is kept up to date.
Additionally, the IMS Manager is responsible for:

- Managing the certification body interface for ISO 27001 and ISO9001 certification.
- Keeping the IMS Management Team advised of the Information Security / Quality / Data Privacy measures required to ensure compliance with Company policy.
- Liaising with external consultants.
- Arranging the regular IMS management meetings.
- Ensuring the CSIP (Continual Service Improvement Plan) is reviewed and updated regularly.
- Incorporating IMS documentation into the company IMS and managing documentation changes.
- Managing the Company internal Audit Programme.
- First point of contact for staff queries and incident logging.

